go_data.justification: GM-CSF and TNF-alpha cooperate in the generation of dendritic Langerhans cells
CD34+ hematopoietic progenitors from human cord blood differentiate along two independent dendritic cell pathways in response to GM-CSF+TNF-alpha
GM-CSF is used in combination with other factors to induce differentiation of various cell types, implying it has cytokine activity
